{"id": "1493430544996892672", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "702167871144591461", "author_name": "_venush", "content": "N: The nigredo (blackening) is associated with death, but hardly ever physical death,!along the lines of depression and endings. When things seem bleak and a phase of life is coming to an end, the darkest before the dawn. In alchemy, there was a saying about the \"white foliated earth\" and this was a symbol of way the darkness becomes whiteness... which is another way of saying the negredo proceeds the albido, which is a spiritualization that comes after the negredo.\n\nTawil: The albedo (Whitening) is that \"dawn\" after darkness . When darkness clears and you have a spiritual awakening. The problem with the albedo, though, is spiritual awakenings cannot be lived in life (Tawil can’t freely walk through Kadath in fear of Supreme Will). A spiritual experience is a peak moment that is, by nature, extremely fleeting. In order to make that spiritual moment last and come into reality and be something you can live, there has to be the rubedo.\n\nThais: The rubedo (Reddening), when a spiritual truth becomes real wisdom, when you walk the walk instead of talk the talk. Spiritual truths aren't any good unless you know when to use them. The right truth in the wrong moment is worthless.", "timestamp": "2026-04-14T01:59:48.525000+00:00"}
